#### toy2.csv - Toys!<br><span class="tag">\#cross-sectional</span>

This example builds on one from the USMR course, where the lectures explored linear regression with a "toy dataset" looking at how **hours of practice influences the reading age** of different toy characters (see [USMR Week 7 Lecture](https://uoepsy.github.io/usmr/2324/lectures/lecture06.html#/learning-to-read-1){target="_blank"}). Here, we broaden our scope to the investigation of how practice affects reading age for **all** toys (not just Martin's Playmobil characters).  

Data are available at [https://uoepsy.github.io/data/toy2.csv](https://uoepsy.github.io/data/toy2.csv){target="_blank"} containing information on 129 different toy characters that come from a selection of different families/types of toy.   


